---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Scrabble Words from Desserts — Sweet Terms That Score Big"
  description="Dessert and pastry words valid in Scrabble with full scoring. SOUFFLE (10pts), WAFFLE (15pts), BISCUIT (11pts). Sweet vocabulary for competitive Scrabble players."
  keywords="scrabble dessert words, souffle scrabble points, waffle scrabble, biscuit scrabble, pastry terms scrabble, sweet words scrabble, bakery vocabulary scrabble"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Words from Desserts — Sweet Terms That Score Big","description":"Dessert and pastry words valid in Scrabble with full scoring. SOUFFLE (10pts), WAFFLE (15pts), BISCUIT (11pts).","datePublished":"2026-06-30","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-from-desserts"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Is WAFFLE a valid Scrabble word?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! WAFFLE scores 15 points (W=4, A=1, F=4, F=4, L=1, E=1). The double-F combined with W=4 makes it one of the highest-scoring dessert words. Valid in both TWL and SOWPODS."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can you play SOUFFLE in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. SOUFFLE scores 10 points (S=1, O=1, U=1, F=4, F=4, L=1, E=1) as a 7-letter word. Without the accent, it's valid. As a 7-letter word, it's a bingo candidate worth 60 total points."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is BISCUIT valid in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! BISCUIT scores 11 points (B=3, I=1, S=1, C=3, U=1, I=1, T=1) as a 7-letter word. Another natural bingo candidate worth 61 points total with the 50-point bonus."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1"><a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span><span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span></nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words from Desserts — Sweet Terms That Score Big</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400"><time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><span>5 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a></div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Dessert vocabulary is surprisingly powerful in Scrabble. Pastry terms are loaded with F tiles (worth 4 each), double letters, and W tiles. From waffles to souffles, these sweet words deliver consistent mid-to-high scores — and many are natural bingo candidates at 7 letters.</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">15 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">WAFFLE (Top)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">14 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">TOFFEE</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">11 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">BISCUIT</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">10 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">SOUFFLE</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">High-Scoring Dessert Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Top Scorer</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">WAFFLE — 15 Points</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">W=4, A=1, F=4, F=4, L=1, E=1 · 6 letters · Double F power</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">A batter cake cooked in a hinged iron. WAFFLE stacks W=4 with two F=4 tiles for 15 points from 6 tiles — one of the best ways to dump two F tiles simultaneously.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🧁 BISCUIT</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">11 pts · B=3, I=1, S=1, C=3, U=1, I=1, T=1 · 7-letter bingo</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🥮 SOUFFLE</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">10 pts · S=1, O=1, U=1, F=4, F=4, L=1, E=1 · 7-letter bingo</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🍬 TOFFEE</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">14 pts · T=1, O=1, F=4, F=4, E=1, E=1 · Double F + double E</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🍩 DOUGHNUT</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">13 pts · D=2, O=1, U=1, G=2, H=4, N=1, U=1, T=1 · 8 letters</p></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Bakery and Pastry Terms</h2>
      <p>Baking vocabulary gives reliable mid-value plays with common tile combinations:</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">PASTRY</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">11pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">FUDGE</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">10pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">TRUFFLE</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">13pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">MOUSSE</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">8pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">CRUMPET</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">13pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">COOKIE</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">12pts</span></span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">More Sweet Scrabble Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🍫 PRALINE</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">9 pts · P=3, R=1, A=1, L=1, I=1, N=1, E=1 · Nut confection</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🍮 CUSTARD</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">10 pts · C=3, U=1, S=1, T=1, A=1, R=1, D=2 · Egg dessert</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🍰 CARAMEL</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">11 pts · C=3, A=1, R=1, A=1, M=3, E=1, L=1 · Burnt sugar</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🧇 FROSTING</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">12 pts · F=4, R=1, O=1, S=1, T=1, I=1, N=1, G=2 · Icing</p></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy for Dessert Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">WAFFLE dumps two F tiles:</span> Drawing two F tiles is awkward. WAFFLE (15pts) and TOFFEE (14pts) are your best escapes. Keep W or T ready when you see double-F.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">BISCUIT and SOUFFLE are bingos:</span> Both 7 letters. BISCUIT (61pts total) and SOUFFLE (60pts total) give you bingo options from dessert vocabulary alone.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">COOKIE uses K well:</span> COOKIE (12pts) places K=5 naturally. When you draw K with common vowels and C, think sweets before obscure words.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Dessert words specialise in <span class="text-white font-medium">double-letter plays</span> — WAFFLE (FF), TOFFEE (FF+EE), COOKIE (OO). They're your best vocabulary for dumping awkward duplicate tiles while still scoring 10-15 points.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find every valid dessert word instantly — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center"><a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a></div>
      <!-- Related Articles -->
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-700 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-gardening/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Gardening</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-halloween/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Halloween</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-jewelry/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Jewelry</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-astronomy/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Astronomy</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-maritime/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Maritime</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>

    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
